content.text:
Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. Let me present the complete design plan.

---

# PipelineTab Rebuild -- Complete Design Plan

## 1. PROBLEM ANALYSIS

The current PipelineTab has three sections stacked vertically:
1. A progress header (works fine, keep it)
2. A tiny horizontal "Pipeline Flow" bar (mini boxes with arrows -- too compressed, no detail)
3. Stacked AgentCards (vertical accordion list)

The core problems:
- **No visual left-to-right flow** -- the agent cards are stacked vertically, losing the pipeline metaphor entirely
- **Phase 0 DONE tasks are invisible** -- Claude Code's 8/8 shows as "complete" but its tasks are collapsed by default; users must click to see them
- **No live agent data** -- the PipelineTab does not call `fetchProjectAgents()` at all; the SessionsTab does, but the data is isolated there
- **No blocked reasons** -- the `blockedReason` field exists in the type but `pipeline-parser.ts` never populates it (line 273: it is never set in the push)
- **No document preview** -- clicking documents does nothing; there is no API endpoint to fetch file content
- **No dependency visualization** -- there is no concept of what blocks what beyond the simple "prereq agents" check

---

## 2. ARCHITECTURE DESIGN

### 2.1 Component Hierarchy (new PipelineTab.tsx)

```
PipelineTab (root)
  |-- PipelineHeader (overall progress -- largely kept from current)
  |-- PipelineSwimlane (new -- the main horizontal layout)
  |     |-- AgentColumn (one per agent, laid out in flex-row)
  |     |     |-- AgentColumnHeader (icon, name, status badge, progress ring)
  |     |     |-- AgentTaskList (scrollable task list within column)
  |     |     |     |-- TaskChip (individual task, color-coded by status)
  |     |     |-- AgentDocList (compact document badges)
  |     |     |-- LiveActivityBadge (when agent has active session)
  |     |     |-- BlockedBanner (when status=blocked, shows reason)
  |-- AgentDetailDrawer (slide-up/right panel when column is clicked)
  |     |-- DrawerTasksSection
  |     |-- DrawerDocumentsSection
  |     |     |-- DocumentRow (clickable -- triggers preview)
  |     |-- DrawerLiveActivitySection (live event feed from agent-monitor)
  |-- DocumentPreviewModal (full-screen overlay for file content)
```

### 2.2 Data Flow

```
PipelineTab
  |-- useQuery('pipeline', projectName)     --> PipelineData (30s refetch)
  |-- useQuery('agents-project', projectName) --> AgentActivity[] (5s refetch)
  |-- useQuery('doc-content', path)          --> string (on-demand, no auto-refetch)
  |
  |-- Merge: match AgentActivity[] to PipelineAgent[] by role name heuristic
  |       BA / BA Agent  --> 'BA' column
  |       Claude Code    --> 'Claude Code' column  
  |       etc.
  |
  |-- State: selectedAgent (null | string) --> controls drawer open/close
  |-- State: previewDoc (null | {name, path}) --> controls document modal
```

### 2.3 Agent-to-Session Matching

The agent monitor returns sessions with a `projectName` field. To match these to pipeline agent roles, we use a heuristic based on the session's recent events. For the MVP, we simply show all live sessions for the project in a sidebar or within the selected agent's drawer. A more advanced version could use the `currentTool` and `lastMessage` to infer which role is active.

---

## 3. SERVER CHANGES

### 3.1 pipeline-parser.ts -- Add blockedReason

In the status determination block (around line 260-267), when `status = 'blocked'`, compute the reason:

```typescript
// After determining status = 'blocked':
if (status === 'blocked') {
  const blockingAgents = prereqAgents
    .filter(pa => {
      const paTasks = agentTasks.get(pa.name) ?? [];
      return paTasks.length > 0 && !paTasks.every(t => t.status === 'DONE');
    })
    .map(pa => pa.name);
  blockedReason = `Waiting for ${blockingAgents.join(', ')}`;
}
```

Then pass `blockedReason` into the `agents.push(...)` call at line 273.

### 3.2 pipeline-parser.ts -- Add dependency edges (new field)

Add a new field to `PipelineData`:

```typescript
export interface PipelineDependency {
  from: string;    // Agent role name (upstream)
  to: string;      // Agent role name (downstream)
  status: 'satisfied' | 'blocking';  // Whether upstream is complete
}
```

Compute dependencies from the pipeline order: each agent depends on all agents with a lower `pipelineOrder` that have tasks. Return these as `dependencies: PipelineDependency[]` on the `PipelineData` response.

### 3.3 server/src/index.ts -- Add document content endpoint

New endpoint: `GET /api/projects/:name/documents/:docPath`

```typescript
app.get('/api/projects/:name/documents/:docPath', async (req, res) => {
  const clean = req.params.name!.replace(/[/\\]/g, '');
  const docName = path.basename(req.params.docPath!);  // prevent traversal
  const fullPath = path.join('/mnt/c/.netapps', clean, docName);

  try {
    const content = await readFile(fullPath, 'utf-8');
    const fileStat = await stat(fullPath);
    res.json({
      name: docName,
      content: content.slice(0, 100_000),  // limit to 100KB
      sizeBytes: fileStat.size,
      lastModified: fileStat.mtime.toISOString(),
    });
  } catch {
    res.status(404).json({ error: 'Document not found' });
  }
});
```

### 3.4 Types additions (both server and frontend)

Add to `PipelineData`:

```typescript
export interface PipelineData {
  agents: PipelineAgent[];
  dependencies: PipelineDependency[];  // NEW
  currentPhase: string;
  currentPhaseId: string;
  overallProgress: number;
  totalTasks: number;
  completedTasks: number;
}
```

Add to frontend `types/index.ts`:

```typescript
export interface PipelineDependency {
  from: string;
  to: string;
  status: 'satisfied' | 'blocking';
}

export interface DocumentContent {
  name: string;
  content: string;
  sizeBytes: number;
  lastModified: string;
}
```

### 3.5 api.ts -- Add fetchDocumentContent

```typescript
export async function fetchDocumentContent(
  projectName: string,
  docPath: string,
): Promise<DocumentContent> {
  return fetchJson<DocumentContent>(
    `/projects/${encodeURIComponent(projectName)}/documents/${encodeURIComponent(docPath)}`
  );
}
```

---

## 4. FRONTEND COMPONENT DESIGN -- DETAILED

### 4.1 PipelineHeader (mostly preserved from current)

Keep the existing glass-card with overall progress bar. Small enhancement: add phase label with a pulsing dot for the active phase.

```tsx
<div className="glass-card rounded-xl p-5">
  <div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
    <div>
      <h3 className="font-heading text-sm font-semibold text-brand-peach">Agent Pipeline</h3>
      <p className="text-xs text-text-muted mt-0.5">
        Current phase: <span className="text-brand-teal font-medium">{pipeline.currentPhase}</span>
      </p>
    </div>
    <div className="text-right">
      <div className="text-2xl font-heading font-bold text-brand-teal">{pipeline.overallProgress}%</div>
      <div className="text-[10px] text-text-muted">{pipeline.completedTasks}/{pipeline.totalTasks} tasks</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div className="h-3 rounded-full bg-surface-elevated overflow-hidden">
    <div className="h-full rounded-full bg-gradient-to-r from-brand-teal to-brand-blue" 
         style={{ width: `${pipeline.overallProgress}%` }} />
  </div>
</div>
```

### 4.2 PipelineSwimlane (new core component)

This is the main horizontal layout. It uses `flex flex-row` with `overflow-x-auto` for horizontal scrolling.

```tsx
<div className="glass-card rounded-xl p-5">
  <h3 className="font-heading text-xs font-semibold text-text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">
    Pipeline Flow
  </h3>
  <div className="flex gap-3 overflow-x-auto pb-2 min-h-[340px]">
    {pipeline.agents.map((agent, i) => (
      <React.Fragment key={agent.role.name}>
        <AgentColumn
          agent={agent}
          liveSession={matchedSessions.get(agent.role.name)}
          isSelected={selectedAgent === agent.role.name}
          onClick={() => setSelectedAgent(
            selectedAgent === agent.role.name ? null : agent.role.name
          )}
        />
        {i < pipeline.agents.length - 1 && (
          <DependencyArrow
            status={getDependencyStatus(agent, pipeline.agents[i + 1])}
          />
        )}
      </React.Fragment>
    ))}
  </div>
</div>
```

### 4.3 AgentColumn (the heart of the redesign)

Each column is a vertical card, ~180px wide, full height of the swimlane. The visual treatment changes dramatically based on status:

**Layout (top to bottom):**
1. Status indicator (top bar -- color strip)
2. Agent icon + name + status badge
3. Progress ring (circular, not bar)
4. Task summary (3/8 done) with mini task dots
5. Top 3-5 tasks shown as chips (scrollable if many)
6. Document count badge
7. Live activity indicator (if agent has active session)
8. Blocked reason (if blocked)

**Status-based styling:**

| Status | Background | Border | Glow | Animation |
|--------|-----------|--------|------|-----------|
| complete | `bg-status-compliant/5` | `border-status-compliant/30` | none | checkmark icon |
| active | `bg-brand-teal/5` | `border-brand-teal/30` | `glow-teal` | pulse on dot |
| blocked | `bg-status-warning/5` | `border-status-warning/30` | none | none |
| idle | `bg-surface-card` | `border-border-subtle` | none | none |

```tsx
function AgentColumn({ agent, liveSession, isSelected, onClick }: AgentColumnProps) {
  const sc = STATUS_CONFIG[agent.status];
  const Icon = ROLE_ICONS[agent.role.name] ?? Users;
  const doneTasks = agent.tasks.filter(t => t.status === 'DONE');
  const todoTasks = agent.tasks.filter(t => t.status !== 'DONE');

  return (
    <button
      onClick={onClick}
      className={`
        flex flex-col w-[180px] min-w-[180px] rounded-xl border p-4 
        transition-all duration-300 cursor-pointer shrink-0
        ${sc.bg} ${sc.border}
        ${agent.status === 'active' ? 'glow-teal' : ''}
        ${isSelected ? 'ring-2 ring-brand-teal ring-offset-2 ring-offset-surface-dark' : ''}
        hover:border-brand-teal/50
      `}
    >
      {/* Status top bar */}
      <div className={`h-1 -mx-4 -mt-4 mb-3 rounded-t-xl ${
        agent.status === 'complete' ? 'bg-status-compliant' :
        agent.status === 'active' ? 'bg-brand-teal' :
        agent.status === 'blocked' ? 'bg-status-warning' :
        'bg-surface-elevated'
      }`} />

      {/* Icon + Name */}
      <div className="flex items-center gap-2 mb-2">
        <div className={`p-1.5 rounded-lg ${sc.bg}`}>
          <Icon size={16} className={sc.text} />
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4 className="font-heading text-xs font-semibold text-text-primary">{agent.role.name}</h4>
          <span className={`text-[9px] font-mono uppercase ${sc.text}`}>{sc.label}</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      {/* Progress circle */}
      <div className="flex justify-center my-3">
        <ProgressRing progress={agent.progress} status={agent.status} size={56} />
      </div>

      {/* Task count */}
      <div className="text-center mb-2">
        <span className={`text-lg font-heading font-bold ${sc.text}`}>
          {agent.completedTasks}/{agent.totalTasks}
        </span>
        <span className="text-[10px] text-text-muted block">tasks</span>
      </div>

      {/* Mini task dots (visual summary) */}
      <div className="flex flex-wrap gap-0.5 justify-center mb-3">
        {agent.tasks.slice(0, 20).map(task => (
          <div
            key={task.id}
            className={`w-2 h-2 rounded-full ${
              task.status === 'DONE' ? 'bg-status-compliant' :
              task.status === 'IN_PROGRESS' ? 'bg-brand-teal' : 'bg-surface-elevated'
            }`}
            title={task.task}
          />
        ))}
      </div>

      {/* Documents count */}
      {agent.documents.length > 0 && (
        <div className="flex items-center gap-1 justify-center text-[10px] text-text-muted mb-2">
          <FileText size={10} className="text-brand-peach" />
          {agent.documents.length} doc{agent.documents.length !== 1 ? 's' : ''}
        </div>
      )}

      {/* Live session indicator */}
      {liveSession && (
        <div className="flex items-center gap-1 justify-center mt-auto pt-2 border-t border-border-subtle">
          <div className="relative">
            <div className="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-status-compliant" />
            <div className="absolute inset-0 w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-status-compliant animate-ping opacity-50" />
          </div>
          <span className="text-[9px] text-status-compliant font-mono">LIVE</span>
        </div>
      )}

      {/* Blocked reason */}
      {agent.blockedReason && (
        <div className="mt-2 p-1.5 rounded bg-status-warning/10 text-center">
          <span className="text-[9px] text-status-warning">{agent.blockedReason}</span>
        </div>
      )}
    </button>
  );
}
```

### 4.4 ProgressRing (circular progress indicator)

A lightweight SVG-based circular progress ring:

```tsx
function ProgressRing({ progress, status, size = 56 }: { progress: number; status: string; size?: number }) {
  const strokeWidth = 4;
  const radius = (size - strokeWidth) / 2;
  const circumference = 2 * Math.PI * radius;
  const offset = circumference - (progress / 100) * circumference;

  const strokeColor = status === 'complete' ? 'var(--color-status-compliant)' :
                      status === 'active' ? 'var(--color-brand-teal)' :
                      status === 'blocked' ? 'var(--color-status-warning)' :
                      'var(--color-text-muted)';

  return (
    <svg width={size} height={size} className="transform -rotate-90">
      <circle
        cx={size / 2} cy={size / 2} r={radius}
        fill="none"
        stroke="var(--color-surface-elevated)"
        strokeWidth={strokeWidth}
      />
      <circle
        cx={size / 2} cy={size / 2} r={radius}
        fill="none"
        stroke={strokeColor}
        strokeWidth={strokeWidth}
        strokeDasharray={circumference}
        strokeDashoffset={offset}
        strokeLinecap="round"
        className="transition-all duration-700"
      />
      <text
        x={size / 2} y={size / 2}
        textAnchor="middle" dominantBaseline="central"
        className="transform rotate-90 origin-center"
        fill="var(--color-text-primary)"
        fontSize="12" fontFamily="var(--font-heading)" fontWeight="600"
      >
        {progress}%
      </text>
    </svg>
  );
}
```

### 4.5 DependencyArrow (between columns)

```tsx
function DependencyArrow({ status }: { status: 'satisfied' | 'blocking' | 'neutral' }) {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 self-center">
      <div className={`flex items-center gap-0.5 ${
        status === 'satisfied' ? 'text-status-compliant' :
        status === 'blocking' ? 'text-status-warning' : 'text-text-muted'
      }`}>
        <div className={`w-6 h-0.5 ${
          status === 'satisfied' ? 'bg-status-compliant' :
          status === 'blocking' ? 'bg-status-warning/50' : 'bg-border-subtle'
        }`} />
        <ArrowRight size={12} />
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}
```

### 4.6 AgentDetailDrawer (expandable below the swimlane)

When a user clicks a column, a detail panel slides open below the swimlane (not a sidebar -- this keeps the tab layout simple and avoids z-index issues).

```tsx
{selectedAgent && (
  <div className="glass-card rounded-xl p-5 animate-fade-in">
    <AgentDetailDrawer
      agent={pipeline.agents.find(a => a.role.name === selectedAgent)!}
      liveSession={matchedSessions.get(selectedAgent)}
      projectName={projectName}
      onPreviewDoc={(doc) => setPreviewDoc(doc)}
      onClose={() => setSelectedAgent(null)}
    />
  </div>
)}
```

The drawer has three sections in a grid layout:

**Left column (tasks):**
```tsx
<div className="space-y-2">
  <h4 className="text-[10px] text-text-muted uppercase tracking-wider flex items-center gap-1">
    Tasks ({agent.completedTasks}/{agent.totalTasks})
  </h4>

  {/* Group by phase */}
  {Object.entries(groupTasksByPhase(agent.tasks)).map(([phase, tasks]) => (
    <div key={phase}>
      <h5 className="text-[10px] font-mono text-brand-teal mb-1">{phase}</h5>
      {tasks.map(task => <TaskRow key={task.id} task={task} />)}
    </div>
  ))}
</div>
```

**Middle column (documents):**
```tsx
<div className="space-y-2">
  <h4 className="text-[10px] text-text-muted uppercase tracking-wider flex items-center gap-1">
    <FileText size={10} /> Documents ({agent.documents.length})
  </h4>
  {agent.documents.map(doc => (
    <button
      key={doc.name}
      onClick={() => onPreviewDoc(doc)}
      className="w-full flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg bg-surface-elevated 
                 hover:bg-surface-hover transition-colors text-left group"
    >
      <FileText size={12} className="text-brand-peach shrink-0" />
      <div className="flex-1 min-w-0">
        <span className="text-xs text-text-primary font-mono truncate block group-hover:text-brand-teal">
          {doc.name}
        </span>
        <span className="text-[10px] text-text-muted">
          {doc.sizeKb}KB -- {formatDistanceToNow(new Date(doc.lastModified), { addSuffix: true })}
        </span>
      </div>
      <Eye size={12} className="text-text-muted group-hover:text-brand-teal" />
    </button>
  ))}
</div>
```

**Right column (live activity):**
```tsx
<div className="space-y-2">
  <h4 className="text-[10px] text-text-muted uppercase tracking-wider flex items-center gap-1">
    <Zap size={10} /> Live Activity
  </h4>
  {liveSession ? (
    <div className="space-y-2">
      <div className="p-2 rounded-lg bg-status-compliant/5 border border-status-compliant/20">
        <div className="flex items-center gap-1 mb-1">
          <div className="relative">
            <div className="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-status-compliant" />
            <div className="absolute inset-0 w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-status-compliant animate-ping opacity-50" />
          </div>
          <span className="text-[10px] font-mono text-status-compliant">ACTIVE</span>
          {liveSession.duration && <span className="text-[10px] text-text-muted ml-auto">{liveSession.duration}</span>}
        </div>
        <p className="text-xs text-text-secondary truncate">{liveSession.lastMessage}</p>
      </div>

      {/* Recent events feed */}
      <div className="space-y-1 max-h-48 overflow-y-auto">
        {liveSession.recentEvents.slice(-10).reverse().map((event, i) => (
          <div key={i} className="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[10px] text-text-muted">
            {event.type === 'tool_use' ? (
              <Terminal size={8} className="text-brand-teal shrink-0" />
            ) : (
              <MessageSquare size={8} className="text-text-muted shrink-0" />
            )}
            <span className="truncate">{event.summary}</span>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  ) : (
    <p className="text-[10px] text-text-muted italic">No active sessions</p>
  )}
