# PipelineTab Rebuild -- Complete Design Plan

## 1. PROBLEM ANALYSIS

The current PipelineTab has three sections stacked vertically:
1. A progress header (works fine, keep it)
2. A tiny horizontal "Pipeline Flow" bar (mini boxes with arrows -- too compressed, no detail)
3. Stacked AgentCards (vertical accordion list)

The core problems:
- **No visual left-to-right flow** -- the agent cards are stacked vertically, losing the pipeline metaphor entirely
- **Phase 0 DONE tasks are invisible** -- Claude Code's 8/8 shows as "complete" but its tasks are collapsed by default; users must click to see them
- **No live agent data** -- the PipelineTab does not call `fetchProjectAgents()` at all; the SessionsTab does, but the data is isolated there
- **No blocked reasons** -- the `blockedReason` field exists in the type but `pipeline-parser.ts` never populates it (line 273: it is never set in the push)
- **No document preview** -- clicking documents does nothing; there is no API endpoint to fetch file content
- **No dependency visualization** -- there is no concept of what blocks what beyond the simple "prereq agents" check

---

## 2. ARCHITECTURE DESIGN

### 2.1 Component Hierarchy (new PipelineTab.tsx)

```
PipelineTab (root)
  |-- PipelineHeader (overall progress -- largely kept from current)
  |-- PipelineSwimlane (new -- the main horizontal layout)
  |     |-- AgentColumn (one per agent, laid out in flex-row)
  |     |     |-- AgentColumnHeader (icon, name, status badge, progress ring)
  |     |     |-- AgentTaskList (scrollable task list within column)
  |     |     |     |-- TaskChip (individual task, color-coded by status)
  |     |     |-- AgentDocList (compact document badges)
  |     |     |-- LiveActivityBadge (when agent has active session)
  |     |     |-- BlockedBanner (when status=blocked, shows reason)
  |-- AgentDetailDrawer (slide-up/right panel when column is clicked)
  |     |-- DrawerTasksSection
  |     |-- DrawerDocumentsSection
  |     |     |-- DocumentRow (clickable -- triggers preview)
  |     |-- DrawerLiveActivitySection (live event feed from agent-monitor)
  |-- DocumentPreviewModal (full-screen overlay for file content)
```

### 2.2 Data Flow

```
PipelineTab
  |-- useQuery('pipeline', projectName)     --> PipelineData (30s refetch)
  |-- useQuery('agents-project', projectName) --> AgentActivity[] (5s refetch)
  |-- useQuery('doc-content', path)          --> string (on-demand, no auto-refetch)
  |
  |-- Merge: match AgentActivity[] to PipelineAgent[] by role name heuristic
  |       BA / BA Agent  --> 'BA' column
  |       Claude Code    --> 'Claude Code' column  
  |       etc.
  |
  |-- State: selectedAgent (null | string) --> controls drawer open/close
  |-- State: previewDoc (null | {name, path}) --> controls document modal
```

### 2.3 Agent-to-Session Matching

The agent monitor returns sessions with a `projectName` field. To match these to pipeline agent roles, we use a heuristic based on the session's recent events. For the MVP, we simply show all live sessions for the project in a sidebar or within the selected agent's drawer. A more advanced version could use the `currentTool` and `lastMessage` to infer which role is active.

