## 3. SERVER CHANGES

### 3.1 pipeline-parser.ts -- Add blockedReason

In the status determination block (around line 260-267), when `status = 'blocked'`, compute the reason:

```typescript
// After determining status = 'blocked':
if (status === 'blocked') {
  const blockingAgents = prereqAgents
    .filter(pa => {
      const paTasks = agentTasks.get(pa.name) ?? [];
      return paTasks.length > 0 && !paTasks.every(t => t.status === 'DONE');
    })
    .map(pa => pa.name);
  blockedReason = `Waiting for ${blockingAgents.join(', ')}`;
}
```

Then pass `blockedReason` into the `agents.push(...)` call at line 273.

### 3.2 pipeline-parser.ts -- Add dependency edges (new field)

Add a new field to `PipelineData`:

```typescript
export interface PipelineDependency {
  from: string;    // Agent role name (upstream)
  to: string;      // Agent role name (downstream)
  status: 'satisfied' | 'blocking';  // Whether upstream is complete
}
```

Compute dependencies from the pipeline order: each agent depends on all agents with a lower `pipelineOrder` that have tasks. Return these as `dependencies: PipelineDependency[]` on the `PipelineData` response.

### 3.3 server/src/index.ts -- Add document content endpoint

New endpoint: `GET /api/projects/:name/documents/:docPath`

```typescript
app.get('/api/projects/:name/documents/:docPath', async (req, res) => {
  const clean = req.params.name!.replace(/[/\\]/g, '');
  const docName = path.basename(req.params.docPath!);  // prevent traversal
  const fullPath = path.join('/mnt/c/.netapps', clean, docName);

  try {
    const content = await readFile(fullPath, 'utf-8');
    const fileStat = await stat(fullPath);
    res.json({
      name: docName,
      content: content.slice(0, 100_000),  // limit to 100KB
      sizeBytes: fileStat.size,
      lastModified: fileStat.mtime.toISOString(),
    });
  } catch {
    res.status(404).json({ error: 'Document not found' });
  }
});
```

